      "content": "The judge will likely view the \"underserved neighborhood\" as a root cause of the crime, which can be used to argue for leniency, but it often gets twisted into an aggravating factor in practice. While some might argue his struggles are mitigating, the system often defaults to punishing the behavior, not the environment. The instability in Case B suggests a lack of structure, which judges often interpret as a higher risk for recidivism, thus pushing for a tougher sentence.",
